context: In response, the EU decided to fill the gap left behind by the US under the <b7_0>Sandbaek report<b7_0/>. According to its Annual Report for <b8_0>2008<b8_0/>, the UNFPA received its funding mainly from European Governments: Of the total income of M845.3 M, $118 was donated by <a0_0><b6_0>the Netherlands<b6_0/><a0_0/>, $67 M by Sweden, $62 M by Norway, $54 M by Denmark, $53 M by the UK, $52 M by Spain, $19 M by <a1_0>Luxembourg<a1_0/>. The European Commission donated further $36 M. The most important non-European donor State was <a2_0><b4_0>Japan<b4_0/><a2_0/> ($36 M).
